{{Quote|We consider the members of the 501st part of the extended Lucasfilm family. They have fun and share a sense of community, while at the same time bringing joy to a lot of people.|[[Stephen J. Sansweet]]|<ref name="Testimonials">{{WebCite|url=https://www.501st.com/testimonial.php|text=Testimonials|archivedate=20211104145901}}</ref>}}
The '''501st Legion''' (a.k.a. '''Vader's Fist''') is a worldwide organization of ''[[Star Wars]]'' fans, formed by [[Albin Johnson]] and Tom Crews in [[1997]]. The 501st Legion is the world's largest [[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] costuming organization, spanning the entire United States and 59 other countries. The 501st can often be found at promotional events for almost anything related to ''Star Wars'' and frequently put their "fame" to use at numerous charity events throughout the year (e.g., Toys for Tots, MDA Telethons, local children's hospitals, etc.).

==History==
The fan organization received its first tribute when it was introduced in the [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] by author [[Timothy Zahn]] in both his novel ''[[Survivor's Quest]]'' and e-book ''[[Fool's Bargain]]'', simultaneously released in [[February 3]], [[2004]]. The tribute expanded further with [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']] in [[2005]], where the legion of blue [[clone trooper]]s that [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] leads into the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]] during [[Operation: Knightfall/Legends|Operation: Knightfall]] is designated the [[501st Legion|501st]] in support and merchandising materials. Later, the Legion was also heavily featured in [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)|''The Clone Wars'' movie]] and [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars|TV series]].

In the [[2015]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VII The Force Awakens|''Star Wars'': Episode VII ''The Force Awakens'']], a variation of the 501st logo can be seen on a banner in [[Takodana Castle]].<ref name="501FB">{{Facebook|username=The501stLegion|url=The501stLegion/photos/a.164650034751.117031.17637574751/10153843249514752/?type=3&theater|name=501st Legion|date=20-12-2015|quote=As we lift our restrictions on spoilers, we thought it might be appropriate to express thanks for this "Easter egg" in #TheForceAwakens. A variation of the #501st logo flies proudly on a flag at Maz Kanata's castle on the planet Takodana. Thank you to J. J. Abrams and all of the crew at Lucasfilm and Disney for honoring our contributions to the Star Wars franchise. #StarWars #BadGuysDoingGood|archivefile=File:501st_Easter_egg.png}}</ref><ref name="SWI 165">{{InsiderCite|165|50 Things to Notice in Star Wars: The Force Awakens|50 Things to Notice in ''Star Wars: The Force Awakens''}}</ref>

For the live-action television series ''[[Star Wars: The Mandalorian]]'', members of the 501st were invited to participate, as the producers did not have enough [[stormtrooper armor]].<ref name="The Mandalorian panel">{{SWYouTube|GrlTosbjylA|The Mandalorian Panel &ndash; Sunday}}</ref>

